ExcelAlmaLookup.title: Broken vertical bar character causes error when using Chinese (Taiwan) locale

comments.body: Fixed in release v1.1.1.  Hard-coded instances of the broken bar character were replaced with ChrW(166).  Also, the registry object had to be created in a different way, using GetObject("winmgmts:{impersonationLevel=impersonate}!\\.\root\default:StdRegProv") and its methods GetStringValue and SetStringValue.  This is because bars were being used is separators in the field sets and URL lists, but the Chinese locale was converting them to solid bars.  This was only happening when using WScript.Shell/RegRead/RegWrite, but not with the new implementation.

orangelight.title: [Suggestion] Use Atkinson Hyperlegible Font - greater readability and legibility for low vision readers

comments.body: @christinach Atkinson Hyperlegible only has support for Latin script based languages and it does not support Greek language, I know because I am working right now on adding Greek language support to [Atkinson Hyperlegible Pro](https://github.com/jacobxperez/atkinson-hyperlegible-pro) you may find the progress report in issue [Missing: Greek Language Support](https://github.com/jacobxperez/atkinson-hyperlegible-pro/issues/38).
